````markdown
# Movies

Representative movies of the generalized cellular automaton (GCA) self-organizing from maximally disordered initial configurations. Three movies are hosted here; two additional large-file movies are available on the Youk Lab website (see below).

---

## Movies in this folder

### TW3_8fps.avi
A 20 × 20 lattice initialized from a maximally disordered configuration and self-organizing into a rectilinear traveling wave. Cell states are color-coded (one of four colors corresponding to the four discrete gene-expression states). Played at 8 frames per second.

---

### color_representation.mp4
A 16 × 16 lattice initialized from a maximally disordered configuration and self-organizing into a rectilinear traveling wave. Cell states are color-coded (one of four colors). This movie and `phase_representation.mp4` below show the same CA trajectory under two different representations of cell state.

---

### phase_representation.mp4
The same trajectory as `color_representation.mp4`, with cell states now represented as a discrete phase field. Each of the four cell states is assigned a phase (0, π/2, π, or 3π/2). Non-white cells mark positions where at least one nearest neighbor differs by a π-phase — these are cells belonging to vortex cores. Watching the vortex-core cells over time reveals the three-stage dynamics described in the paper: rapid vortex creation from the initial disorder, followed by a descending staircase of pairwise vortex annihilations, followed by the emergence of the final rectilinear wave once all vortices have vanished.

---

## Additional movies (hosted externally)

The following movies are available at **[https://www.youklab.org/koopmans_data.html](https://www.youklab.org/koopmans_data.html)** and are too large to host on GitHub:

