| `TW2_8fps.avi` | 109.5 MB | Rectilinear wave formation from a maximally disordered initial configuration. Played at 8 frames per second. |

---

## Notes on the representations

**Color representation**: each of the four discrete gene-expression states — (low, low), (low, high), (high, high), and (high, low) secretion rates of molecule 1 and molecule 2 — is assigned one of four colors, as shown in Fig. 1b of the manuscript. This is the "raw" view of the cellular automaton dynamics.

**Phase representation**: the same four states are recoded as phases 0, π/2, π, and 3π/2, converting the lattice into a discrete phase field. Non-white cells are those that differ by exactly π from at least one nearest neighbor; these mark the boundaries of vortex cores. The topological structure of the dynamics — vortex creation, Brownian diffusion, and pairwise annihilation — is visible in this representation but entirely invisible in the color representation. See Fig. 2a of the manuscript and Supplementary Note 3 for further detail.
````
